<HEAD>Theft of No-Parking Sign in Front of Mayor's House Ends in Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two of Mayor Richard M. Daley's security guards
nabbed a young man after he took a ``No Parking'' sign from in front
of the mayor's house, authorities said.
   Christopher Vajgert, 21, was arrested Monday on a misdemeanor
charge of theft of city property, said police Officer Emily Siwek.
   The two guards stationed outside Daley's house spotted Vajgert
taking the portable sign. They chased him and he was arrested after
a short foot race.
