<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Go-CartFatal     09-05 0083</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Go-Cart Fatal,0085</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Dies in Go-Cart Race</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EMPORIUM, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An out-of-control go-cart struck a curb
during a race and hurled the driver 80 feet, killing him,
authorities said.
   Edward Scott Jr., 43, of Butler, was killed Monday during the
Formula K Grand Prix Invitational Race in this northwestern
Pennsylvania town, police said.
   There were no injuries to other participants or spectators.
   Carts are capable of reaching 85 mph, but police said they
weren't sure how fast Scott was traveling.
