<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     09-05 0690</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0709</SECOND>
<HEAD>Heavy Rains in Northern Florida Causes Some Flooding</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms dumped rain from northern Florida and southern
Georgia to the central Gulf Coast region early today, causing
flooding in some areas. Elsewhere, snow was forecast tonight in the
northern Rockies.
   On Monday, Sandlewood, Fla., received more than 6 inches of rain,
with nearly 3 inches falling in a one-hour period. Jacksonville
Beach, Fla., had nearly 5 inches of rain on top of nearly 2 inches
that fell on Sunday. Street flooding was reported at Sandlewood and
Jacksonville.
   Moisture from the Gulf of California continued to stream
northward and help produce showers and thunderstorms over New
Mexico. Some of the rainfall was locally heavy. Cloudcraft, N.M.,
for instance, received over three-quarters of an inch of rain.
   Showers and thunderstorms developed early this morning across
southeast Colorado, north-central Oklahoma and south-central Kansas.
A flash flood watch was in effect for central and south-central
Kansas.
   Hurricane Gabrielle grew stronger today over the middle Atlantic,
packing 130 mph winds as it churned toward Puerto Rico and the
Virgin Islands.
   Gabrielle's center was expected to pass north of the islands
today, thrusting hurricane-force winds of at least 74 mph as far as
100 miles northward.
   In Montana, a winter storm watch was posted for tonight and
Wednesday in higher elevations. A cold front was expected to bring
snow to the northern Rockies.
   A large high pressure system centered off the coast of Maine
brought clear skies and cool temperatures to much of the northeast
quarter of the nation.
   The high in the nation Monday was 113 degrees at Borrego Springs,
Calif.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms scattered
from the eastern Gulf of Mexico region and Florida to the middle
Mississippi Valley, Kansas and the northern Rockies; snow over the
northern Rockies; and strong and gusty winds across Wyoming.
   Predicted highs: in the 60s over southeast New England and from
north-central Montana to Washington state; in the 70s from Oregon
into the northern Intermountain region, from the Great Lakes region
to the northern and middle Atlantic Coast and along the California
coast; in the 90s from Florida across the lower Mississippi Valley,
the southern Plains, portions of the central and southern Rockies,
the southern Plateau into interior California and over western
portions of South Dakota and Nebraska; near 100 degrees from central
Texas to the Rio Grande Valley; from 100 to 115 degrees over the
desert Southwest; and in the 80s over much of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 37
degrees at Yellowstone, Wyo., to 92 degrees at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y., 53 fair; Atlanta 68 fair; Boston 56 fair;
Buffalo 58 cloudy; Charleston, S.C., 76 showery; Chattanooga 66
fair; Cincinnati 68 cloudy; Cleveland 66 cloudy; Detroit 68 partly
cloudy; Hatteras 75 showery; Jacksonville 72 fair; Key West 84 fair;
Knoxville 66 fair; Macon 71 partly cloudly; Miami 80 partly cloudy;
New York 54 fair; Philadelphia 59 fair; Pittsburgh 59 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine, 46 fair; Richmond 62 partly cloudly; Tampa 76 fair;
Washington, D.C., 62 fair.
   _Central: Birmingham 71 fair; Bismarck 51 fair; Denver 70 fair;
Des Moines 64 fair; Fort Worth 83 fair; Indianapolis 68 foggy;
Kansas City 66 foggy; Little Rock 72 hazy; Louisville 71 foggy;
Memphis 75 hazy; Nashville 71 fair; New Orleans 79 showery; North
Platte 58 partly cloudy; Oklahoma City 76 partly cloudy; Omaha 63
fair; Rapid City 62 fair; St. Louis 71 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 58
fair; Sault Ste. Marie 57 fair; San Antonio 82 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 67 windy; Anchorage 52 rain; Boise 63 fair;
Casper 57 fair; Fairbanks 56 cloudy; Great Falls 58 fair; Honolulu
78 fair; Las Vegas 80 fair; Los Angeles 64 fair; Medford 61 fair;
Pendleton 66 windy; Phoenix 90 fair; Portland, Ore., 59 partly
cloudy; Reno 64 fair; Salt Lake City 62 fair; San Diego 68 fair; San
Francisco 53 fair; Seattle 59 partly cloudy; Spokane 59 fair.
   _International: Calgary 48 showery; Montreal 57 fair; Ottawa 57
partly cloudy; Regina 54 fair; Toronto 66 partly cloudy; San Juan 83
fair.
