<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--EscapeAttempt     09-05 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Escape Attempt,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Inmate Killed; Bedsheet Rope Was Too Shote</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST MEADOW, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An inmate was killed during an escape
attempt when his bedsheet rope turned out to be too short and he
fell 35 feet, police said.
   William Sibila, 34, of New Hyde Park, had been held in the prison
ward of the Nassau County Medical Center for observation since June
23 after being arrested on a robbery charge, said county police
spokesman Officer Charles Koller.
   Sibila pried off the grating from his 10th-floor window Monday
night and tried to use a string of bedsheets to lower himself to a
fourth-floor landing 55 feet below, Koller said. But the rope was
short and Sibila fell to the landing, hit his head and was
pronounced dead at the scene, police said.
</TEXT>
