<FIRST>r a PM-Bakker-Dortch     09-05 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bakker-Dortch,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ex-Bakker Associate Leaves Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Rev. Richard W. Dortch, who is
expected to testify against Jim Bakker at the TV evangelist's fraud
trial, is out of the hospital after a five-day stay for an
undisclosed ailment.
   Attorney George Tragos said Dortch, 57, was released Monday from
Morton Plant Hospital. He said the family asked that Dortch's
condition remain confidential.
   ``But I'm sure that if the government requires, he will
testify,'' Tragos added.
   The former PTL vice president was sentenced Aug. 24 to eight
years in prison and fined $200,000 after pleading guilty to fraud at
the evangelical empire Bakker built. Dortch agreed to testify
against Bakker.
   A federal judge in North Carolina suspended Bakker's trial
Thursday and committed him to a federal mental ward for psychiatric
evaluation after a psychiatrist reported Bakker was hallucinating
and cowering under a couch.
   It is not known when the trial will resume.
</TEXT>
