<HEAD>British Soccer Hooligans Arrested After Fight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested five British soccer fans
who rampaged through a Stockholm restaurant and started a fight with
some Swedes, national radio said Tuesday.
   Two of the fans, here for the World Cup qualifying match between
England and Sweden on Wednesday, faced charges of assault and
causing material damage, the radio said.
   The disturbance started at a restaurant late Monday, when two of
the youths caused considerable damages. Later in the evening, all
five started a fight with a group of Swedes, according to the
national news agency TT.
   Police released three of the fans after a few hours, but two were
detained until Tuesday morning for questioning and to sober up.
   Twenty British soccer fans were taken off a Sweden-bound
passenger ferry Monday, which had to return to Harwich, England,
after widespread disorder. One fan was believed drowned after having
jumped overboard during the trip.
