<HEAD>Four Killed in Rest Home Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMIENS, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out early Tuesday at a
retirement home and killed four residents, firefighters said.
   The victims, three men and a woman aged 63 to 70, were asleep on
the third floor of the Chateau de Caix retirement home near Amiens,
north of Paris.
   The fire broke out on the floor about 2:30 a.m. and filled the
area with smoke, suffocating the four sleeping residents,
firefighters said. The remaining occupants were evacuated without
injury.
   The cause of the fire was not known, but firefighters said it
appeared to be accidental.
   About 40 people live at the home.
