<FIRST>r i AM-Pakistan-Crash     09-05 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Pakistan-Crash,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pakistani F-16 Crashes, Kills Pilot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S.-built F-16 jet fighter of the
Pakistan Air Force crashed during a training mission, and the pilot
was killed, military officials said Tuesday.
   The military issued a statement saying the jet went down Monday
near Jhang, 175 miles south of Islamabad, the capital.
   Squadron Leader Zafar Ahsan was killed, but there was no damage
or injuries on the ground, the military said. An investigation was
under way.
   Pakistan acquired 50 of the F-16s in 1985. Three have crashed,
including one that hit a wild pig on a runway.
   The United States has agreed to sell Pakistan 60 more of the jets.
