<HEAD>Chile Files Protest With Soviets Over Fishing Dispute</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chile, which has had no diplomatic
relations with the Soviet Union since Gen. Augusto Pinochet came to
power in a 1973 coup, filed a protest with the Soviets, claiming
their trawlers have been fishing illegally in Chilean waters, the
Foreign Ministry said Tuesday.
   Ministry spokesman Carlo Ducci said the protest was relayed
