<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Student-Gun     09-05 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Student-Gun,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Student Arrested After Carrying Gun to School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A seventh-grader was removed from class and
arrested Tuesday for bringing a gun to school, authorities said.
   Marion County Sheriff's Department dispatcher Rick McGuire said
the 14-year-old boy was taken to the juvenile center. The exact
charges against him were not known.
   Terry Dorman, assistant principal at Keystone Middle School, said
the revolver was found Friday in a jacket that was left in a
classroom. On Tuesday, school officials discovered the jacket
belonged to the seventh-grader and called the sheriff's department,
Dorman said.
   Once the student returns to school, ``there will be some
discipline that will have to be administered,'' he said, but that
had not been determined Tuesday.
   ``He told us he felt like he needed it for protection in his
community,'' Dorman said. The boy, who is new at school this year,
is from an inner city area and is bused to the suburban school,
Dorman said. School began Aug. 23.
   Dorman said nothing was said to the other students about the
incident.
</TEXT>
