<FIRST>r w AM-BRF--Egypt-USWarships 1stLdWritethru a0536 09-05 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Egypt-US Warships, 1st Ld Writethru, a0536,160</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Aircraft Carrier, Other Warships Transit Suez Canal</HEAD>
<HEAD>PRECEED Suez, Egypt; to include detail from Pentagon announcement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The aircraft carrier USS America and three
other warships headed through the Suez Canal on Tuesday to join the
U.S. 6th Fleet in the Mediterranean, the Pentagon said.
   The carrier is slated to replace the USS Coral Sea, which has
been on duty in the Mediterranean and is to return to the United
States to prepare for a decommissioning.
   The America has been with the U.S. 7th Fleet in the Indian Ocean
area for the past three months.
   It was to be accompanied through the canal by the guided missile
cruiser USS Dale, the destroyer USS Compte De Grasse and the frigate
USS Joseph Hewes, the Pentagon said.
   The statement added that the USS Mobile Bay, a guided missile
cruiser, the guided missile destroyer USS Lawrence and the combat
support ship USS Seattle were due to return to the United States
with the Coral Sea.
</TEXT>
