<FIRST>r i AM-Chile-Killing     09-05 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Chile-Killing,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Radical Leftist Leader Assassinated in Chile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Assassins in a car riddled the chief
spokesman of the radical Leftist Revolutionary Movement with
submachine-gun fire, hitting him at least 12 times and killing him
instantly, police reported Tuesday.
   They said Jecar Neghme, 29, was shot at about 10 p.m. Monday as
he walked toward his group's headquarters in a residential
neighborhood near the city center.
   No one claimed responsability.
   The Movement, known as MIR, was organized in the mid-1960s by a
group of dissident young Communists and quickly became Chile's main
urban guerrilla organization.
   In recent years, the group split and a faction led by Neghme and
others abandoned armed struggle and was organizing as a formal
political party, still following a radical leftist line.
</TEXT>
