<SECOND>BC-PRI--License Requirements, Adv 07,0325</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv07</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Thursday, Sept. 7, and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>States' Age-Based Driver License and Renewal Requirements</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-PRI--Older Drivers, BC-PRI--Drivers-Program</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of age-based licensing and
renewal procedures as of last January, based on an April report by
the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration.
   No age-specific requirements were reported for the other states.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ALASKA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.
   ARIZONA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.
   CALIFORNIA: No good-driver renewal-by-mail or test waivers at 70.
   DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA: Knowledge and road tests for renewal after
75; reaction test for renewal at 70.
   HAWAII: License renewal every two years after 65, every 4 years
for others.
   ILLINOIS: Under legislation signed into law Aug. 31, license
renewal starting in 1990 will be every two years for those 81-86,
every year for 87 and above, every four years for others; road test
for license or renewal at 75, effective immediately.
   INDIANA: License renewal every three years after 75, every four
years for others; road skills test for renewal after 75.
   IOWA: Renewal every two years after 70, every four years for
others.
   LOUISIANA: Renewal every two years after 70, every five years for
others.
   MAINE: Vision test for renewal at 40 and 52 and each renewal
after 65.
   MARYLAND: Medical report for new drivers at 70 and above.
   NEW HAMPSHIRE: Knowledge and road skills tests for renewal after
75.
   NEW MEXICO: Renewal every year after 75, every four years for
others.
   OREGON: Vision test at renewal over 50.
   PENNSYLVANIA: Physical examination for a sample of renewal
applicants over 45 (usually the drivers are over 65.)
   RHODE ISLAND: Renewal every two years after 70, every five years
for others.
   UTAH: No good-driver vision test waiver at renewal over 65.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sept. 7</NOTE>
