<FIRST>r f BC-Goodrich-Culligan     09-05 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Goodrich-Culligan,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>BFGoodrich Agrees to Buy Culligan's Arrowhead Industrial Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   BFGoodrich Co. has agreed in principle to
acquire Arrowhead Industrial Water, which provides high purity water
equipment to industries, BFGoodrich said Tuesday.
   Terms of the sale, subject to a definitive agreement and
government approval, were not disclosed.
   Arrowhead, based in Lincolnshire, Ill., has seven facilities
serving the United States market and has about 250 employees and
annual sales of $35 million. It is a subsidiary of Culligan
International Co. of Northbrook, Ill.
   Arrowhead designs, makes, installs and services high purity water
systems to power generating plants, computer manufacturers and other
industries requiring very high purity water supplies.
   ``BFGoodrich already participates in the ultra-high purity water
treatment market as a supplier of reverse osmosis chemicals and
services,'' said Kent H. Lee Jr., president of BFGoodrich's
speciality polymers and chemicals division.
</TEXT>
