increased { to 57{, Arco gained | to 105\. Amoco fell [ to 48\ and
Exxon was down [ to 43~. Among most active issues, Bristol Meyers
was up | to 50}, IBM gained | to 118, General Motors was up [ to 50[
and Chrysler fell \ to 26}. Teledyne lost 3{ to 372\, Coca Cola fell
1[ to 66[ and International Paper dropped 1[ to 57|.
   Ford, which is holding talks with the Swedish automaker and
aerospace company Saab-Scania, lost | to 53|.
   Last week, the Dow average soared to new highs amid an upbeat
attitude about the nation's economy. Several reports showed
continued economic strength, including the August employment report,
which buoyed market sentiment.
   The news indicated that the economy isn't slowing as much as
expected, which has raised fears that the Federal Reserve may raise
interest rates instead of lowering them.
   The Dow industrials Friday rose 14.82 to a new high of 2,752.09,
surpassing the previous peak of 2,743.36 reached a week ago.
   The nation's financial markets were closed Monday for the Labor
Day holiday.
