<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic steel production totaled 1.706 million
net tons during the week ending Sept. 2, 1989, up 1 percent from the
previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute reported
Tuesday.
   The week's production represented 76.8 percent of the industry's
domestic capacity, according to the steel industry group.
   American steelmakers produced 1.908 million net tons in the same
week last year, AISI said.
   Domestic steel production so far this year is 67.545 million net
tons, 0.3 percent above last year's production at this time, AISI
said.
