<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Like modern-day conquistadors, foreign airlines
are descending on the New World to buy up pieces of U.S. carriers.
   Major U.S. airlines have become hot properties, stalked by
big-time investors, unions and rival carriers. Foreign airlines are
keen to get in on the action, and the Americans are eager to get the
infusions of capital from abroad.
   More important, though, the foreigners are taking equity stakes
in order to help them gain access to the booming U.S. air travel
market, which can augment their passenger traffic.
