over a $200 million buyout offer from a group of the fast-food
restaurant chain's franchisees.
   Roberts, who indicated he favored the buyout offer that was
rejected by Posner, sent a sharply worded letter to Posner on Monday
in which he resigned as vice chairman of the board and a director of
Posner's DWG Corp.
   That company owns 60 percent of Chesapeake Financial Corp., of
