<FIRST>r f BC-Obit-Hopton     09-05 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Obit-Hopton,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lester C. Hopton, Former Ingersoll-Rand President, Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lester C. Hopton, a former president of
Ingersoll-Rand Co., has died at his Florida home. He was 87.
   Hopton, who died Monday, began working at Ingersoll-Rand in 1926
while still a student at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.
   He started in the accounting department at the company's
Phillipsburg, N.J., plant and worked his way through the ranks as
general factory controller, comptroller and, in 1955, president.
   In 1967, at the age of 65, Hopton retired as president but stayed
on the board of directors until 1974.
   Ingersoll-Rand, based in Woodcliff Lake, N.J., is a leading
manufacturer of heavy machinery and industrial equipment.
   Hopton is survived by his wife, Phylis Pack Hopton, two children,
four grandchildren and two great-grandchildren.
</TEXT>
